y of George A. Lucas, vol. 2, p. 163). This watercolor was likely hanging in Walters' Baltimore townhouse from 1885 (“The Walters Art Collection, Recent Additions – Barye, Millet, Bonnat – Bonvin’s Water Colors,” Baltimore Sun, 1 February 1886, p. 4.), described in R.B. Gruelle's catalogue of the gallery \"Notes Critical and Biographical\" (1895), p. 190.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/37.1529","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PS4_37.1529_Fnt_DD_AT21_23603-tms.jpg"},{"ObjectID":6468,"Title":"Garment Decoration (\"\"Segmentum\"\") with Man Killing Panther","Artist":"6640","Date":"4th-5th century (Early Byzantine)","Medium":"wool, linen","CreditLine":"Estate of D.G. Kelekian. Walters Art Museum, 1951, by purchase.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/83.685","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PL7_83.685_Fnt_BW.jpg"},{"ObjectID":6993,"Title":"Nogaku zue","Artist":"14996|6252","Date":"1899 (Meiji)","Medium":"pigments on mulberry paper","CreditLine":"Walters Art Museum, 1989, by gift.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/95.270","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PS3_95.270_Fnt_DD_JP09.jpg"},{"ObjectID":8393,"Title":"Anatomical Figure of a Woman","Artist":"6211","Date":"1600-1650 (Renaissance)","Medium":"cast bronze","CreditLine":"Walters Art Museum, 1931, by bequest.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/54.317","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PS1_54.317_Fnt_DD_T11.jpg"},{"ObjectID":9093,"Title":"Cup","Artist":"3812","Date":"about 1888","Medium":"Translucent enamel, gold","CreditLine":"Walters Art Museum, 1931, by bequest.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/44.571","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PL9_44.571_Fnt_SL_T86.jpg"},{"ObjectID":9443,"Title":"Crow","Artist":"4905","Date":"1775-1825 (late Edo)","Medium":"iron","CreditLine":"Walters Art Museum, 1931, by bequest.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/52.159","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PL7